x^2y^2+y^2z^2+z^2x^2=xyz
x,y,z>0
\frac {xy}z+\frac{yz}x+\frac{zx}y=1
x,y,z>0
\frac {xy}z+\frac {yz}x=\cos^2\theta
\frac{zx}y=\sin^2\theta
\frac {xy}{z\cos^2\theta}+\frac {yz}{x\cos^2\theta}=1
\frac {xy}{z\cos^2\theta}=\cos^2\phi
\frac {yz}{x\cos^2\theta}=\sin^2\phi
\frac {xy}{z\cos^2\theta},\frac {yz}{x\cos^2\theta}>0
\frac {xy}z=\cos^2\theta\cos^2\phi--->(1)
\frac {yz}x=\cos^2\theta\sin^2\phi--->(2)
\frac{zx}y=\sin^2\theta--->(3)
xyz=\cos^4\theta\cos^2\phi \sin^2\phi \sin^2\theta-->(4) 
(4)/(1),z^2=\cos^2\theta\sin^2\phi \sin^2\theta\implies z=\cos\theta\sin\phi \sin\theta=\frac{\sin\phi \sin2\theta}2
(4)/(2)
(4)/(3)
x=\frac{\cos\phi \sin2\theta}2
y=\cos\phi\sin\phi \cos^2\theta
x,y,z>0
\sin2\theta, \sin\phi,\cos\phi>0\implies 0<\phi<\frac{\pi}2
0<2\theta<\pi
\theta\ne \frac{\pi}2
\sin2\theta, \sin\phi,\cos\phi<0\implies \pi<\phi<\frac{3\pi}2
\pi<2\theta<2\pi
\theta\ne \frac{3\pi}2
